    <stitle>9 SPEED AND 10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON 16709 AND 16710 SERIES - AIR SYSTEM - SLAVE VALVES (Figure 6)
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="x1302103" svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="1">
        <title>SLAVE VALVES (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1302106">Figure 6</hotlnk>)
        </title>
        <figure id="f1302106" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302106" filename="../figg13/g1302106.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 6. Bolt Piston-Type Poppet-Type</caption>
        </figure>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1302106">Figure 6</hotlnk>
            for disassembly and reassembly of the piston-type slave valve assemblies. Should the poppet-type slave valve
            assembly prove to be defective, replace the complete assembly, as it is non-serviceable. The actuating
            components used with these valve assemblies are non-interchangeable. Failure to use the correct plunger pin,
            spring, and alignment sleeve during installation on the transmission will cause hard shifting in Low Range
            gears.
        </para>
